E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons Movie
E4Plus1.uk.description: (2007) Animated comedy. When Homer's love for a pig causes world-threatening pollution, Springfield gets enclosed in a huge dome. D'oh! Will he do the decent thing and save his neighbours?

E4Plus1.uk.title: New: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Brand new series - Bart's Birthday: Bart has to organise his own birthday party when Homer forgets to post the invitations. Mr Burns fakes his own death. (S36 Ep1/18)

E4Plus1.uk.title: New: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Brand new series - The Yellow Lotus: The Simpsons stumble across a mystery and an old enemy while they're on holiday at a peculiar island resort. Dr Hibbert drugs an otter. (S36 Ep2/18)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Free Guy
E4Plus1.uk.description: (2021) Comedy action starring Ryan Reynolds. Guy lives in Free City. Free City isn't real. Nor is Guy. It's all a big online game. Can he take down the corrupt game publisher?

E4Plus1.uk.title: Gogglebox
E4Plus1.uk.description: The series continues with Stranger Things, Strictly, Celebrity Scam Interceptors, Malice, Songs of Praise, CBeebies Bedtime Stories and Animals on Drugs. (S26 Ep13) [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: Gogglebox
E4Plus1.uk.description: This time the Goggleboxers watch: Strictly, Changing Ends, One Shot with Ed Sheeran, All Her Fault, The Marvellous Miniature Workshop and Sara Davies' Christmas Craft Off. (S26 Ep14) [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: First Dates
E4Plus1.uk.description: Helicopter pilot Paul, who's also a cross-dresser, embarks on his first date in women's clothing. 'Sexy geeks' Hannah and Dan bond over video games and shared insecurities. (S11 Ep8) [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: Naked Attraction
E4Plus1.uk.description: Nameya is after both beauty and brains: will she find her perfect package in a sexy guy or her first ever girlfriend? Dan loves a fairy-tale, but she's yet to find her leading man. (S9 Ep2)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Inbetweeners
E4Plus1.uk.description: Caravan Club: The boys call Jay's bluff and go to the Camber Sands meeting of the Caravan Club to see if it really is a massive sex party. Jay's dad gives them advice about sex. (S1 Ep5/6)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Inbetweeners
E4Plus1.uk.description: Xmas Party: It's the end of term and Will has been voted chairman of the Christmas prom committee, so he ropes in Simon, Jay and Neil to help get things organised. (S1 Ep6/6)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Change Constant: Sheldon and Amy stay up late awaiting a phone call that could bring big news from the Nobel Committee: are their lives about to change? (S12 Ep23)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Stockholm Syndrome: Howard and Bernadette go on a trip without their children, Leonard and Penny try to keep a secret, and Raj makes a new friend. (S12 Ep24)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Hollyoaks Omnibus
E4Plus1.uk.description: An unexpected present sends the Hutchinsons' Christmas into turmoil. Jack has an extra-special mission up his sleeve. And while the sparkle fades for Mercedes, Theresa's wish is granted. [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: Hollyoaks
E4Plus1.uk.description: There's festive cheer in the Hutchinson household this Christmas, but an unexpected present sends the day into turmoil... Meanwhile, Jack has an extra-special mission up his sleeve.

E4Plus1.uk.title: Hollyoaks
E4Plus1.uk.description: There's Christmas magic at the McQueens', but for Mercedes, the sparkle has faded... Can Warren help to spread festive cheer? Meanwhile, a knock on the door grants Theresa's wish.

E4Plus1.uk.title: Rude(ish) Tube Shorts
E4Plus1.uk.description: A short, cheeky clip from Rude Tube's naughty little sister, Rude(ish) Tube, featuring sports of the lawnmower, motorbike and bicycle variety.

E4Plus1.uk.title: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares USA
E4Plus1.uk.description: Fleming: Gordon Ramsay visits Fleming, a Danish restaurant in Miami. It was once the best family-run restaurant in town but is now losing money fast. (S3 Ep6) [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares USA
E4Plus1.uk.description: Sushi Ko: Akira and Lisa are losing up to $20,000 a month at their sushi restaurant in California. Can Gordon piece the family back together and save the restaurant? (S3 Ep7) [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Goldbergs
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Age of Darkness: The family rally round to comfort Erica when she's dumped by her boyfriend Drew. Barry becomes addicted to an arcade video game. (S1 Ep21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Goldbergs
E4Plus1.uk.description: A Wrestler Named Goldberg: Murray coaches Barry for his first high school wrestling match but keeps it a secret from Beverly, who is sure to disapprove. (S1 Ep22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Behind the Laughter: A behind-the-scenes look at the Simpson family. How did they win their fame? And how did they cope when the showbiz pressure got too much? (S11 Ep22/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Kiss Kiss, Bang Bangalore: Mr Burns outsources the plant to India and puts Homer in charge of training the workforce. Patty and Selma kidnap a celebrity. (S17 Ep17/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Lisa Gets the Blues: Lisa gets the yips and Bart is made to dress up and sing as Annie from the musical. They go to New Orleans to recover. (S29 Ep17/21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 30: The Convention Conundrum: E4 bids a fond farewell to Big Bang with a countdown of our top 30 episodes. First up, Sheldon decides to hold his own comic book convention. (S7 Ep14)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 29: The Nerdvana Annihilation: When Penny makes fun of Leonard's habit of collecting goofy memorabilia, his friends kick up a fuss and try to keep him on the side of the nerds. (S1 Ep14)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 28: The Middle Earth Paradigm: Penny's Halloween party puts Leonard, Sheldon, Howard and Raj through a demanding new test of their social skills. (S1 Ep6)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 27: The Maternal Congruence: Leonard is horrified when his mother turns up unannounced for a Christmas visit, and then he finds out that Sheldon knew about her divorce before him. (S3 Ep11)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 26: The Maternal Conclusion: Leonard is surprised when his mother Beverly comes to visit and is kind to him, until he finds out the real reason she's there. (S12 Ep22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 25: The Re-entry Minimization: Howard is disappointed when he doesn't receive a hero's welcome on his return from space. Will he ever get the recognition he deserves? (S6 Ep4)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 24: The Earworm Reverberation: Sheldon is driven to distraction when he can't get a familiar tune out of his head. Howard and Raj find out that their band has a fan. (S9 Ep10)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 23: The Precious Fragmentation: The gang squabble over a ring that they believe was used in The Lord of the Rings movies, and Sheldon seems to be turning into Gollum. (S3 Ep17)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 22: The Cooper Extraction: Sheldon has to go back to Texas when his sister goes into labour. While he's away, the gang gather at the flat to decorate the Christmas tree. (S7 Ep11)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 21: The Tangerine Factor: When Penny breaks up with her boyfriend, Leonard plucks up the courage to ask her out. And each of them turns to Sheldon for advice about their date. (S1 Ep17)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 20: The Intimacy Acceleration: When the gang hear about an experiment designed to make participants fall in love, Sheldon and Penny put it to the test as a joke. (S8 Ep16)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 19: The D & D Vortex: When the gang find out that Wil Wheaton is hosting a celebrity game of Dungeons & Dragons at his home, deception and betrayal take hold. (S12 Ep16)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 18: Pilot: The first ever episode of the hit sitcom. Leonard and Sheldon's geeky world is shaken up by the arrival of a beautiful new neighbour. (S1 Ep1)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 17: The Comic Book Store Regeneration: The gang prepare for the reopening of Stuart's comic book shop. Penny teaches Sheldon to 'let it go' when he is irritated. (S8 Ep15)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 16: The Bakersfield Expedition: The guys get all dressed up for a photo opportunity at a Star Trek location but end up stranded in the desert. (S6 Ep13). The countdown continues tomorrow!

E4Plus1.uk.title: Hollyoaks
E4Plus1.uk.description: Things are frosty between Misbah and Donny this Christmas, but will the festive cheer bring the family closer together? Or will Donny's recent escapades be exposed?

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Homer Is Where the Art Isn't: Homer learns to love a Miro painting. Then it's stolen - and he gets the blame. (S29 Ep12/21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: King Leer: Moe inherits a mattress business from his father, then lands in an all-out war with his siblings. (S29 Ep16/21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Lisa Gets the Blues: Lisa gets the yips and Bart is made to dress up and sing as Annie from the musical. They go to New Orleans to recover. (S29 Ep17/21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Celebrity Gogglebox
E4Plus1.uk.description: On the 'Box this time: Blue Planet II, Unsolved Mysteries, It Chapter Two, Antiques Roadshow, Basic Instinct, and BBC News on face masks. (S2 Ep7)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Celebrity Gogglebox for SU2C
E4Plus1.uk.description: Celebrities including Kieran Culkin and Joe Marler join regulars for Stand Up To Cancer. On the 'Box: Celebrity Catchphrase Christmas Special, The Sound of Music and loads more. (S26 Ep17)

Film4.uk.title: Late Night with the Devil
Film4.uk.description: (2023) Unsettling found-footage horror with David Dastmalchian. A has-been host tries to save his 70s talk show using a demonically possessed 13-year-old girl. Really, what could go wrong?

UAndYesterday.uk.description: Dunbar to Edinburgh: Michael Portillo travels around the British Isles by train and learns about the challenges the coastal regions face, starting at Siccar Point in Berwickshire. S1 Ep1

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Great Coastal Railway Journeys
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Leith to Culross: Michael Portillo continues his Scottish coastal journey along the Firth of Forth at the railway engineering icon for which it's famous, the Forth Bridge. S1 Ep2

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Great Coastal Railway Journeys
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Stirling to East Neuk: Michael Portillo begins this leg of his Scottish railway journey from Dunbar to Peterhead in the beautiful medieval city of Stirling. S1 Ep3

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Great Coastal Railway Journeys
UAndYesterday.uk.description: St Andrews to Stonehaven: Michael Portillo visits Leuchars, known nowadays on the railways as Leuchars for St Andrews, which is Scotland's oldest university. S1 Ep4

UAndYesterday.uk.title: American Pickers
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Space Invaders Smackdown: Mike and Frank's faces light up when they stumble on a warehouse packed with vintage searchlights and Frank risks it all for a game of Space Invaders. S16 Ep20

UAndYesterday.uk.title: American Pickers
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Best Of: Field Trip: Mike and Frank run amok when they find rare relics that deserve to be on display in a museum. S16 Ep21

UAndYesterday.uk.title: American Pickers
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Best Of: Lil' Pickers: Mike and Frank have their work cut out for them when they run into some kid pickers who drive a hard bargain and show them how well they can negotiate. S16 Ep22

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Find It, Fix It, Flog It
UAndYesterday.uk.description: New. Henry Cole and Simon O'Brien head to Newark, where items include an antique European threshing board and a ship's porthole. S2 Ep17

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Find It, Fix It, Flog It
UAndYesterday.uk.description: New. Simon O'Brien creates table lamps from old theatre lights and Henry Cole finds a treat for restorer Guy. S2 Ep18

UAndYesterday.uk.title: The Thin Blue Line
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Rag Week: Laughs with the boys in blue from the mind of Blackadder co-writer Ben Elton and the deadpan delivery of Rowan Atkinson. Fowler faces the stress of student rag week. S1 Ep4

UAndYesterday.uk.title: The Thin Blue Line
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Night Shift: Writer Ben Elton and star Rowan Atkinson are reunited in the comedy about a rather incompetent police force. The station's full of juvenile yobs, but that's CID for you! S1 Ep5

UAndYesterday.uk.title: The Thin Blue Line
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Yuletide Spirit: Incompetent policemen; there's a rich source of comedy material, as Mr Bean transforms into Inspector Fowler. Grim is on the trail of highly dangerous carol singers. S1 Ep7

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Building of Britain
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Mighty Cathedrals: Fred Dibnah uncovers the construction techniques of stonemasons, engineers and carpenters through the ages, focusing on Norman cathedrals. S1 Ep1

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Building of Britain
UAndYesterday.uk.description: The Art of Castle Building: Fred Dibnah tours the coast of north Wales to admire the defensive features and architecture of the castles that helped Edward I subdue the rebellious Welsh. S1 Ep2

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Building of Britain
UAndYesterday.uk.description: The Age of the Carpenter: Fred Dibnah looks at structures from the Middle Ages, visiting England's oldest fortified building with a moat, Stokesay Castle. S1 Ep3

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Building of Britain
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Scottish Style: Fred Dibnah demonstrates the engineering and design skills that shaped Scottish baronial style, visiting buildings of note such as Glamis Castle and the House of Dun. S1 Ep4

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Building of Britain
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Building the Canals: Fred Dibnah explores the work of the builders and engineers responsible for the waterways of Britain, visiting the Leeds-Liverpool and Bridgewater canals. S1 Ep5

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Building of Britain
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Victorian Splendour: Fred Dibnah explores his passion for 19th-century buildings, concentrating on Eastnor Castle in Herefordshire and St Giles's Church in Cheadle. S1 Ep6

UAndYesterday.uk.title: One Foot in the Grave
UAndYesterday.uk.description: The Executioner's Song: Victor just doesn't believe it again as an artistic dispute with the Meldrews threatens to scupper the plans of Patrick (Angus Deayton) for a quiet birthday. S6 Ep1

UAndYesterday.uk.title: One Foot in the Grave
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Tales of Terror: More unlikely quirks of fate conspire to torment retired curmudgeon Victor Meldrew in the classic comedy. A routine medical check-up has sinister implications. S6 Ep2

UAndYesterday.uk.title: One Foot in the Grave
UAndYesterday.uk.description: The Futility of the Fly: The cloth cap-sporting old sourpuss hires a cleaner to help out around the house, which creates more problems than it solves and sets off bizarre events. S6 Ep3

UAndYesterday.uk.title: One Foot in the Grave
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Threatening Weather: A sweltering summer's night during a power cut proves to be a trying time for Victor as a couple decide to test drive Victor's car without actually taking it. S6 Ep4

UAndYesterday.uk.title: One Foot in the Grave
UAndYesterday.uk.description: The Dawn of Man: King of the grumps Victor Meldrew faces more bizarre situations. Victor's decision to take up fishing leads to an encounter with humankind at its most primitive. S6 Ep5

UAndYesterday.uk.title: One Foot in the Grave
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Things Aren't Simple Anymore: The immensely moving final episode of the long-running sitcom, in which uber-grump Victor finally meets his maker. David Renwick leaves us with a twist. S6 Ep6

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Alfa Romeo Giulia/Citroen 2CV6: Derek casts his eye over a Citroen 2CV, before he is off admiring the treasure trove of more than 270 motorbikes in the same garage. S6 Ep1

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Ford Zephyr/Autobianchi: Derek heads off to collect some vintage motorcycles from a garage at the bottom of the garden in the North-East of England. S6 Ep2

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Capri/Alpine/Lancia Fulvia Zagato: Derek heads to Sunderland to pick up a real Italian beauty - a 1972 Lancia Fulvia Zagato. Red and racy, the car has seen better days but Derek's still impressed. S9

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Austin Morris Minor: Up for sale at the Mathewson's auction is a 1275 Mini GT that's come from just down the road and could be a future British icon. S9 Ep3

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's World of Steam, Steel & Stone
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Preserving Our Past: An insight into Fred Dibnah's love of restoring engines and chimneys, highlighting one of his greatest triumphs - his stream traction engine. S1 Ep6

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Teleshopping
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Shopping from Home.

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Great Coastal Railway Journeys
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Forvie to Peterhead: Michael Portillo's Scottish railway journey reaches Aberdeen, from where he heads out to Forvie National Nature Reserve. S1 Ep5

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Great Coastal Railway Journeys
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Inverness to the Cairngorms: Michael Portillo crosses the Culloden Viaduct aboard the Caledonian Sleeper to arrive bright and early in Inverness. S1 Ep6

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Great Coastal Railway Journeys
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Cullen to Cawdor: Michael Portillo travels by train north from Inverness to the Orkney Islands. Beginning on the Moray Firth, Michael admires the Cullen Viaduct. S1 Ep7

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Great Coastal Railway Journeys
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Invergordon to Tain: Michael Portillo's Scottish coastal railway journey reaches Invergordon on the Cromarty Firth, the third great inlet on the northeast coast of the Highlands. S1 Ep8

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's World of Steam, Steel & Stone
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Changing the Landscape: Fred Dibnah's interest in industrial engineering, which was sparked by the canals, railways and bridges built near his Bolton home. S1 Ep9

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's World of Steam, Steel & Stone
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Great British Builders: Fred Dibnah offers demonstrations of building techniques as he shares his appreciation for the skills of the great British builders. S1 Ep10

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's World of Steam, Steel & Stone
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Masters of Their Trade: An insight into Fred Dibnah's appreciation for the craftsmanship of the past and for the work of those people who still carry on the traditions. S1 Ep1

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's World of Steam, Steel & Stone
UAndYesterday.uk.description: A Good Day's Work: The ex-steeplejack shares his enthusiasm for Britain's industrial heritage. In this final programme, Fred visits Warwick Castle and Ely Cathedral. S1 Ep12

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterday.uk.description: The First Railways: Fred Dibnah examines the work of the Stephenson family, and how it influenced the railways. S1 Ep2

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Changing the Landscape: Fred Dibnah explores how railways changed Britain and follows the growth in popularity of the locomotive. Plus, a visit to a rope haulage railway in Derbyshire. S1 Ep3

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Brunal and the Great Western: Fred Dibnah learns more about the work of one of his heroes, engineer Isambard Kingdom Brunel and his plans for a wide gauge railway system. S1 Ep4

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterday.uk.description: The Great Days of Steam: Fred Dibnah explores the creation of the stream train and new speed records that were set in the 1920s. S1 Ep5

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Railway Preservation: Fred Dibnah explains how diesel-powered locomotives replaced steam trains, leading to the creation of the Railway Preservation Society. S1 Ep6

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Historic Railways: Fred Dibnah examines historic railways and engineering projects undertaken by the likes of Stephenson and Hackworth. S1 Ep7

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Narrow Gauge Railways: Fred Dibnah visits Ravenglass, Cumbria, where he has an opportunity to see an old mill working. S1 Ep8

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Ffestiniog Railway: Fred Dibnah visits the Ffestiniog Railway in Gwynedd, Wales, where he talks about restoration work and is taken for a ride down the track by the manager Paul. S1 Ep9

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterday.uk.description: The Main Line Experience: Fred Dibnah visits Llangollen Railway, where he reminisces about the past, and is given a chance to fulfil a childhood dream with driver Robert Haslam. S1 Ep10

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Bluebell Railway: Fred Dibnah visits the Bluebell Railway in East Sussex. His first footplate ride of the day is on Fenchurch, where he is pleasantly surprised to meet a fire lady. S1 Ep11

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Railway Yards and Workshops: Fred Dibnah explains what happens in railway works, visiting Bo'ness and Kinneil, Scotland, and the Boston Lodge in Ffestiniog, Wales. S1 Ep12

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Midland Railway: Fred Dibnah visits the Midland Railway Centre in Derbyshire, is given a tour of the sheds and gets to have a go on the hydraulic riveter. S1 Ep13

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Severn Valley Railway: Fred Dibnah drives his own engine to Bridgnorth, Shropshire, to see an engine repair shed and purpose-built boiler shop. S1 Ep14

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Great Central Railway: Fred visits the Great Central Railway, the only remaining main line railway in the country which still has steam locomotives, where he takes a footplate ride. S1 Ep15

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Blue Planet
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Introduction: David Attenborough catalogues life beneath the ocean waves. All manner of spectacular lifeforms dwell deep underwater, from alien monsters to pack-hunting killer whales. S1 Ep1

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Blue Planet
UAndYesterday.uk.description: The Deep: The mysteries of the oceans are revealed in this stunning series narrated by David Attenborough. Among the oddities featured here are terrifying fish with massive teeth. S1 Ep2

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Blue Planet
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Open Ocean: Oceanic explorations, topped off with David Attenborough's masterful narration. Learn about the predatory skills of some of the planet's most charismatic hunters. S1 Ep3

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Blue Planet
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Frozen Seas: David Attenborough salutes the survival techniques of creatures who endure harsh conditions in the Arctic and Antarctic, as the lauded natural history series continues. S1 Ep4

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Blue Planet
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Seasonal Seas: David Attenborough vividly describes the history of our oceans. Seasonal changes in the richest waters on Earth drive an explosion of life, from seals to jellyfish. S1 Ep5

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Fiat Strada Abarth/Austin 10: Dave finds two rare Fiats and a VW Corrado. Derek has his work cut out trying to remove an old Morris that appears to be supporting the garage roof. What could possibly g

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Ford Granada/Toyota Hilux: Derek navigates the dry stone walls of the Peak District to collect a very original 1988 Opel Manta. Plus, Dave deals with a Ford Granada rally support vehicle. S6 Ep4

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Bentley T1/Fiesta XR2: Dave's son Jack is heading out to Cheshire to collect two cars with a 35-year age difference. And luckily for Mathewsons, Lucy knows exactly what has been brought in. S3 Ep10

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Excalibur/Austin 7: A 1970 Excalibur Roadstar, once owned by Roy Orbison, arrives at Thornton le Dale and Derek heads to County Durham to collect a 1935 Austin 7 Ulster that's been rebuilt. S4 Ep1

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Austin A30/BMW Isetta: Two British classics head into to the Mathewsons' auction room, Dave heads to North Manchester to pick up an Austin A30 and a Morris 8 E with an alternative paint job. S4 Ep2

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Teleshopping
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Shopping from Home.

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Great Coastal Railway Journeys
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Lairg to Caithness: The latest stage of Michael Portillo's trek takes him past lochs and castles on the Far North Line to Britain's northernmost railway station at Thurso. S1 Ep9

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Great Coastal Railway Journeys
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Thurso to Orkney: Michael Portillo heads for the ferry port of Scrabster to cross the Pentland Firth to the Orkney Islands. S1 Ep10

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Great Coastal Railway Journeys
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Tynemouth to Bardon Mill: Michael Portillo sets off from Tynemouth on the first leg of a trip to Berwick, hearing about a tragedy that inspired a coastal rescue service. S1 Ep11

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Great Coastal Railway Journeys
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Newcastle to Lynemouth: Michael Portillo heads from Newcastle to Lynemouth, and is intrigued to hear of its part in Newcastle's early industrial development. S1 Ep12

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Lotus Esprit/MG TF/ERF Lorry: On the way to pick up two lovely '70s Lotus sports cars, Derek takes to the skies for his first ever helicopter flight in a 1967 Bell 47 chopper. S9 Ep10

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Moskvitch: Dave's drawn to a Fiat Uno 45 in '1970's beige', with 36,000 miles on the clock. S9 Ep11

UAndYesterday.uk.title: The World at War
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Red Star: Following Operation Barbarossa in 1941, the Soviet Army battled the Germans almost alone for two years. Laurence Olivier recounts their efforts as the epic series continues. S1 Ep11

UAndYesterday.uk.title: The World at War
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Whirlwind: The ultimate guide to World War II, narrated by Laurence Olivier. Bomber Command are unable to hit their targets precisely and attack German cities under cover of darkness. S1 Ep12

UAndYesterday.uk.title: The World at War
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Tough Old Gut: The hugely respected chronology of WWII. Churchill described Italy as the 'soft underbelly of the crocodile', thinking the Allies could cut through it to reach Germany. S1 Ep13

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Jensen Interceptor/Triumph Sprint: Derek auctions off a Jensen Interceptor and a Jensen Healey along with a one-off Wood & Pickett Triumph Dolomite Sprint. S3 Ep1

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Rover 2000 SC/Triumph Spitfire: A 1971 Mercedes SL and a 1989 Jaguar XJS emerge from a barn on a chicken farm, a Roller and a Rover go under the hammer and a 1966 Triumph Spitfire is restored to near

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Planet Earth
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Ocean Deep: Witness our planet in its natural glory. David Attenborough looks at life deep undersea, where a 30-tonne whale shark hunts and vampire squid employ bioluminescence. S1 Ep11

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Planet Earth
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Islands: Wildlife documentary series presented by David Attenborough, beginning with a look at the remote islands which offer sanctuary to some of the planet's rarest creatures. S2 Ep1

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Planet Earth
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Mountains: The wildlife documentary series with David Attenborough continues with a unique and intimate glimpse into the secretive lives of mountain-dwelling animals. S2 Ep2

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Red Dwarf
UAndYesterday.uk.description: The End: The first-ever episode of the space comedy! Meet the crew of the Red Dwarf: sole surviving human Lister, hologram Rimmer, and a lifeform evolved from Lister's cat. S1 Ep1

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Red Dwarf
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Future Echoes: Classic space comedy. Having accelerated for a mere three million years, Red Dwarf breaks through the light barrier and sets off a series of weird occurrences. S1 Ep2

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Red Dwarf
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Balance of Power: Interstellar laughs from the Red Dwarf crew. Lister is desperate to see dead officer Kochanski once more and begs Rimmer to bring her back as a hologram. S1 Ep3

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Mediterranean with Simon Reeve
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Setting off from a snowy mountain ski resort in Cyprus, Simon Reeve finds an island and a capital city still deeply divided between Turkish Cypriots and Greek Cypriots. S1 Ep2

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Frozen Planet
UAndYesterday.uk.description: To the Ends of the Earth: David Attenborough reveals the vast wilderness of the polar regions. At the North Pole, polar bears court and the sun returns after six months of dark. S1 Ep1

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Bedford Bus/Triumph TR7: Derek has a three-hour drive in a 1960s bus that arrived in the UK after a life in the sun. Dave takes a Triumph TR7 convertible to auction. S6 Ep5

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Vanden Plas/Ford Fiesta XR2: Dave's on his way to Grimsby to pick up an iconic 80s fast Ford, the Mk1 Fiesta XR2. S6 Ep6

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: One Foot in the Grave
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: The Exterminating Angel: One of the great TV comic creations - Victor Meldrew. The misery guts gets a new job as a chauffeur and learns the importance of keeping an eye on the tank. S5 Ep5

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Allegro/Ice Cream Van: Derek journeys to Essex to collect Pete Wood's Austin Allegro, which has been sitting in an aircraft hangar at Audley End for 20 years. S12 Ep9

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Aston DB2/Merc SL: Jack's off to East Yorkshire for an iconic 80's motor, where a Ford enthusiast is thinning out his herd of nine Escorts. S12 Ep10

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Bond Bugs/Westfalia/Renault 4/MGB: Derek checks out an abandoned 1985 Renault 4 and an MGB Roadster that hasn't seen the light of day for 36 years, and Jack heads to Rotherham to pick up a pair of rar

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Mini Mayfair/NSU Quickly: In the 100th episode, Derek heads to Northumberland to collect a rare 1975 NSU RO 80, Jack deals with a Mini Mayfair stuck in a barn, and an Aston Martin DBS husk is auctione

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Planet Earth
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Shallow Seas: David Attenborough celebrates our amazing planet. Here we follow a humpback whale and its calf on a journey from a tropical paradise to storm-ravaged icy polar seas. S1 Ep10
